Title: Ballets Russes competition photo gallery
Primary image caption: My brother
Primary image rights information: David
Subjects: and I are dressed in fancy dress for a function at school. It was my last year in Infants School before I went on to Primary School. My mother had made both our outfits. She wasn't a particularly good sewer but I think she has done a pretty good job. I was supposed to be Little Bo Peep
Station: but I seem to have lost my sheep. My outfit was made completely out of crepe paper and Mum had gone to a great deal of trouble in making the hooped skirt and pantaloons. I recall I hated the outfit and didn't want to wear it and much preferred David's Superman costume. It brings back fond memories as my Mum died in 2009 and I miss her greatly. We used this photo in a collage that we put together for her 90th birthday.
State: Copyright: AAP | Source: Brenda Scarfi | Byline:

Title: We have a winner
Primary image caption: Judges comments: FROZEN IN FLIGHT is an amazing photograph that has captured an insect in flight.The image captures the viewers’ imagination as one endeavours to interpret the content within the photograph.Due to the images soft focus
Primary image rights information: we can only assume that this insect is a butterfly.The photographer has use a slow shutter speed to capture the movement of the insect’s wings whilst having the ability to keep the body in sharp focus. The colours within the photograph compliment each other and the blurred background keeps your focus on the main subject being the butterfly. The subject is position nicely in the frame that assists in providing the concept of flight and movement. The overall technique used has allowed this image to be bought to life. Overall an amazing image that is pleasant to view.
Subjects: Copyright: ABC | Source: Flickr | Byline: divweena
Place: ABC New England North West NSW
